1
00:01:38,980 --> 00:01:41,780
[Episode 4]

2
00:01:57,239 --> 00:01:58,280
Do you need help?

3
00:01:58,280 --> 00:02:00,580
No, it's okay.

4
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:24,540
Sit tight.

5
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:36,360
Tell me.

6
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:40,919
Why don't I have
such a beautiful distant cousin?

7
00:02:40,919 --> 00:02:43,219
You have to ask your aunt.

8
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:51,879
There's so much lavender.

9
00:02:51,879 --> 00:02:54,899
Pull over. I want to have a look.

10
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:10,720
The lavender is so pretty.

11
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:12,240
There's so much.

12
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:14,759
It's so pretty.

13
00:03:14,759 --> 00:03:16,640
Is it pretty?

14
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:19,492
It's all right.

15
00:03:21,759 --> 00:03:26,100
Nothing to say to someone
who doesn't appreciate beauty.

16
00:03:27,160 --> 00:03:28,690
What you see is beauty.

17
00:03:28,690 --> 00:03:31,440
It cools you down and clears toxins.
Relieves wind and stops itching.

18
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:33,039
The essential oils and tea bags made of it

19
00:03:33,039 --> 00:03:34,319
can calm you down

20
00:03:34,319 --> 00:03:36,039
and relieve anxiety.

21
00:03:36,039 --> 00:03:38,254
What a killjoy.

22
00:03:38,254 --> 00:03:39,680
I often pass by after work.

23
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:41,660
I'm sick of it.

24
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:45,059
Thank you.

25
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,280
When you're not home,

26
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:03,672
you go to Shunyi for work?

27
00:04:04,480 --> 00:04:07,800
You fix phones and laptops.

28
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,439
You do all sorts of odd jobs.

29
00:04:09,439 --> 00:04:10,978
You must make a lot.

30
00:04:10,978 --> 00:04:12,639
Xuan Island's business is good too.

31
00:04:12,639 --> 00:04:14,400
Why is your family so poor?

32
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,680
You seem to be doing well in Beijing.

33
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:19,440
How did you end up here?

34
00:04:22,658 --> 00:04:23,639
Right.

35
00:04:23,639 --> 00:04:25,399
I heard from Hu

36
00:04:25,399 --> 00:04:26,879
that you have good grades.

37
00:04:26,879 --> 00:04:29,100
Why did you drop out?

38
00:04:31,439 --> 00:04:33,360
Your dad asked someone to send you here.

39
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:35,519
I don't think he wanted you to leave.

40
00:04:35,519 --> 00:04:37,739
Why are you still going abroad?

41
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,439
You...

42
00:04:44,439 --> 00:04:46,894
can't talk nicely, can you?

43
00:04:47,519 --> 00:04:49,600
You have to get an answer
when you ask a question.

44
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:52,000
You end up hurting someone's pride
when you pay.

45
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,800
That's arrogance.

46
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:58,226
You're the one who's prejudiced against me.

47
00:04:58,226 --> 00:05:00,680
I didn't mean to hurt anyone.

48
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:04,639
Besides, I've already apologized
for what I said to your mom the other day.

49
00:05:04,639 --> 00:05:06,800
If you don't want to answer,

50
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:09,720
you can just say no.

51
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:12,259
Okay. I'll say no.

52
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:29,600
Are you done looking?

53
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:31,420
No.

54
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:38,160
Come on.

55
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:39,960
Let's go home.

56
00:06:03,879 --> 00:06:04,959
By the way,

57
00:06:04,959 --> 00:06:07,120
I'll fix the laptop
and bring it back to you tonight.

58
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:09,952
Don't hang around Shunyi so often.

59
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:12,379
Why?

60
00:06:13,399 --> 00:06:15,300
It's troublesome.

61
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:21,360
Is the laptop fixed?

62
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:23,000
- Auntie.
- Ye.

63
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,800
How is it? Can the laptop be fixed?

64
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:26,439
Mr. Ju said it can be fixed.

65
00:06:26,439 --> 00:06:28,759
- Mr. Ju?
- Mr. Ju?

66
00:06:29,759 --> 00:06:31,920
- Xing Wu.
- Uncle Zhao.

67
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:34,080
Mr. Ju?

68
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:40,040
Hu said it'll cost a lot to fix the laptop.

69
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:42,264
Take this first.

70
00:06:42,839 --> 00:06:44,839
No, it's okay. You don't have to pay.

71
00:06:44,839 --> 00:06:46,040
It can be fixed.

72
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:49,240
Just take it back. She doesn't need money.

73
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:51,392
- I hope I'm not holding you up.
- Grandma.

74
00:06:51,392 --> 00:06:54,759
You didn't. Mr. Ju said
it can be fixed quickly.

75
00:06:54,759 --> 00:06:56,400
That's good.

76
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:58,799
I feel bad for causing you so much trouble.

77
00:06:58,799 --> 00:07:00,480
I bought some sea cucumbers for you.

78
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:03,439
Please accept it. I'll feel bad if you don't.

79
00:07:03,439 --> 00:07:04,640
Take it.

80
00:07:04,640 --> 00:07:06,759
Go on.

81
00:07:07,759 --> 00:07:10,879
Okay. I'll take the sea cucumbers.

82
00:07:10,879 --> 00:07:12,520
Take the money back.

83
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:14,280
All right.

84
00:07:14,280 --> 00:07:16,119
I'll hurry back to tell my wife.

85
00:07:16,119 --> 00:07:17,439
Go ahead.

86
00:07:17,439 --> 00:07:18,920
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

87
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:20,160
- I'll get going.
- Bye.

88
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:22,199
Take care.

89
00:07:22,199 --> 00:07:25,439
He's henpecked. His wife keeps the money.

90
00:07:25,439 --> 00:07:28,119
Thank you, Ye.

91
00:07:28,119 --> 00:07:31,319
Well, Hu made a meal for you.

92
00:07:31,319 --> 00:07:32,600
It's hot in the pot.

93
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,960
I'm going next door.

94
00:07:33,960 --> 00:07:34,960
Okay.

95
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:37,154
Help yourself.

96
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:48,439
Since when do you do favors

97
00:07:48,439 --> 00:07:50,679
instead of taking cash?

98
00:07:50,679 --> 00:07:54,380
Sea cucumbers in exchange for a computer?
It's a fair exchange.

99
00:07:56,119 --> 00:07:58,439
Here, good for you.

100
00:07:59,439 --> 00:08:00,799
If you want me to leave Xuan Island
as soon as possible,

101
00:08:00,799 --> 00:08:03,859
then fix the computer quickly.

102
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:08,166
You're welcome.

103
00:08:34,740 --> 00:08:39,328
[Shunyi Repairs]

104
00:08:55,880 --> 00:08:58,221
My favorite.

105
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:22,160
<i>I feel bad for her.</i>

106
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:24,319
<i>Her mom passed away a few years ago.</i>

107
00:09:24,319 --> 00:09:29,099
<i>If it weren't for trouble at home,
her dad wouldn't have sent her here.</i>

108
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:39,779
<i>That's impressive.</i>

109
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:42,319
<i>Where's the money?</i>

110
00:09:42,319 --> 00:09:43,760
<i>Tell me!</i>

111
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:45,280
<i>I'll kill you if you don't.</i>

112
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:48,439
<i>I mean it!</i>

113
00:09:48,439 --> 00:09:49,880
<i>Don't hit my mom!</i>

114
00:09:49,880 --> 00:09:52,559
<i>You were pregnant with another man's child
when you married me.</i>

115
00:09:52,559 --> 00:09:54,439
<i>Have I ever despised you?</i>

116
00:09:54,439 --> 00:09:56,040
<i>Now that my business has failed,</i>

117
00:09:56,040 --> 00:09:57,719
<i>I've been living off you for a few years,</i>

118
00:09:57,719 --> 00:09:59,679
<i>and you despise me for being incompetent?</i>

119
00:09:59,679 --> 00:10:03,210
<i>I'll kill you!</i>

120
00:10:05,799 --> 00:10:07,479
<i>Let go! Let go of me!</i>

121
00:10:07,479 --> 00:10:08,479
<i>Wu!</i>

122
00:10:08,479 --> 00:10:09,839
<i>Are you crazy?</i>

123
00:10:09,839 --> 00:10:13,559
<i>How could you hit your child?</i>

124
00:10:13,559 --> 00:10:16,240
<i>Don't cry.</i>

125
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:19,106
<i>Xing Guo Dong...</i>

126
00:10:22,439 --> 00:10:24,559
<i>Wu. It's fine.</i>

127
00:10:24,559 --> 00:10:26,930
<i>It's fine.</i>

128
00:10:29,799 --> 00:10:31,739
<i>I'm fine.</i>

129
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:06,280
Wu.

130
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:07,599
You must be tired.

131
00:11:07,599 --> 00:11:09,199
Have some skewers.

132
00:11:09,199 --> 00:11:11,160
I bought them from Mr. Zhang.

133
00:11:11,160 --> 00:11:12,439
His TV box is broken.

134
00:11:12,439 --> 00:11:14,360
He wants you to fix it when you have time.

135
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:15,360
Okay.

136
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:17,240
His son broke his leg at a construction site.

137
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:20,719
I don't think they'll pay much.

138
00:11:20,719 --> 00:11:23,280
The engine on Mr. Liu's fishing boat
keeps stalling.

139
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:24,920
He wants you to fix it too.

140
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:26,360
Okay, I got it.

141
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:28,040
I'll make time tomorrow.

142
00:11:28,040 --> 00:11:30,000
Okay.

143
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,240
Tell me.

144
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:33,520
How does it feel to fall from the sky

145
00:11:33,520 --> 00:11:36,078
into the mud?

146
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:39,739
I'd have to fly up into the sky to find out.

147
00:12:15,319 --> 00:12:18,350
It's indeed X-change.

148
00:12:22,319 --> 00:12:23,719
<i>The property certificate is done.</i>

149
00:12:23,719 --> 00:12:26,250
<i>Now you can apply for a visa.</i>

150
00:12:26,920 --> 00:12:30,220
Thank you for helping me.

151
00:12:32,799 --> 00:12:36,019
<i>All set. Just need to sign up for classes.</i>

152
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:44,139
Grandma.

153
00:12:46,839 --> 00:12:48,079
Grandma, it's okay.

154
00:12:48,079 --> 00:12:50,229
I'm here.

155
00:12:50,959 --> 00:12:53,035
I'm here.

156
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:58,220
It's all right.

157
00:13:16,520 --> 00:13:18,921
It's okay.

158
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:47,880
Grandma!

159
00:13:47,880 --> 00:13:50,439
How is she?

160
00:13:50,439 --> 00:13:52,160
She took her medicine.

161
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:53,439
She's asleep.

162
00:13:53,439 --> 00:13:55,683
Okay.

163
00:14:02,319 --> 00:14:04,636
Is your hand okay?

164
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:10,052
I'm fine.

165
00:14:14,240 --> 00:14:16,675
I've fixed the laptop for you.

166
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:19,979
Thank you.

167
00:14:41,640 --> 00:14:44,839
That's great. Everything is here.

168
00:14:44,839 --> 00:14:47,920
Xing Wu doesn't talk nicely.

169
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:50,620
But he's quite skilled.

170
00:15:16,559 --> 00:15:19,240
It's finally done.

171
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:20,920
Congratulations.

172
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:23,873
You've solved a big problem in your life.

173
00:15:25,719 --> 00:15:27,079
Congratulations to you too.

174
00:15:27,079 --> 00:15:30,904
You'll soon get rid of this jinx.

175
00:15:32,480 --> 00:15:35,256
You're quite self-aware.

176
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:37,679
I'm happy today.

177
00:15:37,679 --> 00:15:39,940
I can't be bothered to argue with you.

178
00:15:48,520 --> 00:15:50,360
What?

179
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:52,040
Treat the wound on your hand.

180
00:15:52,040 --> 00:15:55,090
It's hot. It's prone to infection.

181
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:07,640
Thank you for today.

182
00:16:07,640 --> 00:16:09,360
It was nothing.

183
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:12,079
You're welcome.

184
00:16:12,079 --> 00:16:14,760
You seem to know how to help patients.

185
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:16,320
Yes.

186
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:19,959
Because my mom had always been unwell.

187
00:16:19,959 --> 00:16:21,439
Just in case,

188
00:16:21,439 --> 00:16:23,160
I learned a lot

189
00:16:23,160 --> 00:16:25,979
about first aid.

190
00:16:29,640 --> 00:16:31,439
It's just that

191
00:16:31,439 --> 00:16:34,099
she couldn't be saved in the end.

192
00:16:43,599 --> 00:16:45,199
I'm sorry

193
00:16:45,199 --> 00:16:47,426
to remind you of your mom.

194
00:16:53,040 --> 00:16:54,839
It's okay.

195
00:16:54,839 --> 00:16:57,240
It has been a long day. I'm tired.

196
00:16:57,240 --> 00:16:59,489
I'm going to bed.

197
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:04,343
Good night.

198
00:18:20,560 --> 00:18:21,759
You're here.

199
00:18:21,759 --> 00:18:23,719
This is the last dish.

200
00:18:23,719 --> 00:18:27,414
Auntie, is today a special day?

201
00:18:28,199 --> 00:18:30,239
Today is a special day.

202
00:18:30,239 --> 00:18:31,439
It's all my fault.

203
00:18:31,439 --> 00:18:33,519
I was too busy yesterday.

204
00:18:33,519 --> 00:18:35,039
Grandma told me

205
00:18:35,039 --> 00:18:36,999
that you saved her.

206
00:18:36,999 --> 00:18:39,439
And you got hurt.

207
00:18:39,439 --> 00:18:41,439
Our family owes you everything.

208
00:18:41,439 --> 00:18:44,279
So I went out early this morning

209
00:18:44,279 --> 00:18:46,519
and bought fresh stuff

210
00:18:46,519 --> 00:18:47,999
to cook for you.

211
00:18:47,999 --> 00:18:49,439
Is this necessary?

212
00:18:49,439 --> 00:18:51,360
Of course.

213
00:18:51,360 --> 00:18:53,160
Grandma, are you all right?

214
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:54,160
I'm fine.

215
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:56,039
It's just an old ailment.

216
00:18:56,039 --> 00:18:58,869
Thank you for yesterday.

217
00:18:58,869 --> 00:19:00,560
Look.

218
00:19:00,560 --> 00:19:03,920
You suffered.

219
00:19:03,920 --> 00:19:05,080
Wu.

220
00:19:05,080 --> 00:19:07,239
As long as Ye is with us,

221
00:19:07,239 --> 00:19:09,519
you make sure she's comfortable.

222
00:19:09,519 --> 00:19:10,759
Take good care of her.

223
00:19:10,759 --> 00:19:12,759
Otherwise, I'll hold you responsible.

224
00:19:12,759 --> 00:19:15,015
Don't worry, Grandma.

225
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:21,160
Let's eat then.

226
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:23,719
- Here.
- Okay.

227
00:19:23,719 --> 00:19:26,999
Let me get you a shrimp first.

228
00:19:26,999 --> 00:19:29,120
- Thank you, Auntie.
- Fresh squid.

229
00:19:29,120 --> 00:19:31,479
Lan Fang is the best at this.

230
00:19:31,479 --> 00:19:32,640
Okay.

231
00:19:32,640 --> 00:19:34,840
It's really good.

232
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:38,775
Have some soup too.

233
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:59,185
Are you installing an air conditioner for me?

234
00:20:01,441 --> 00:20:02,759
It's a second-hand air conditioner.

235
00:20:02,759 --> 00:20:04,843
Use it for now.

236
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:07,999
It's not a second-hand air conditioner.

237
00:20:07,999 --> 00:20:11,380
It's a major upgrade in quality of life.

238
00:20:59,719 --> 00:21:02,053
Does your hand still hurt?

239
00:21:07,640 --> 00:21:09,822
It's much better.

240
00:21:35,039 --> 00:21:37,479
How long has Grandma been sick?

241
00:21:37,479 --> 00:21:40,199
It started in the past two years.
It's not just seizures.

242
00:21:40,199 --> 00:21:42,279
Her hemiparesis is getting worse too.

243
00:21:42,279 --> 00:21:43,959
Sometimes, she can't remember things.

244
00:21:43,959 --> 00:21:45,279
The brain disease

245
00:21:45,279 --> 00:21:47,959
is prone to all sorts of unexpected events.

246
00:21:47,959 --> 00:21:49,840
That's why

247
00:21:49,840 --> 00:21:53,039
you come home to watch her eat every day.

248
00:21:53,039 --> 00:21:55,279
Because you're worried about her?

249
00:21:55,279 --> 00:21:57,039
Li Lan Fang is impatient.

250
00:21:57,039 --> 00:21:58,679
She often forgets to cook
while playing mahjong.

251
00:21:58,679 --> 00:22:01,107
So I have to keep an eye on her.

252
00:22:01,959 --> 00:22:05,432
You're very good to Grandma.

253
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:07,960
Grandma raised me.

254
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:11,279
I wouldn't be here without her.

255
00:22:11,279 --> 00:22:12,959
You're amazing.

256
00:22:12,959 --> 00:22:14,560
We're about the same age.

257
00:22:14,560 --> 00:22:17,160
You're already the head of the family.

258
00:22:18,160 --> 00:22:19,999
But where's your dad?

259
00:22:19,999 --> 00:22:22,407
I've never seen him.

260
00:22:24,080 --> 00:22:26,043
He's dead.

261
00:22:27,679 --> 00:22:30,640
But I heard he was out there.

262
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:32,600
He's been gone for so long.

263
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:34,160
And he's in debt.

264
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:36,489
He's as good as dead.

265
00:22:56,880 --> 00:22:58,838
All right.

266
00:23:02,959 --> 00:23:04,439
This is so nice.

267
00:23:04,439 --> 00:23:09,640
Now all we need is half a chilled watermelon.
That would be perfect.

268
00:23:09,640 --> 00:23:11,519
Eat.

269
00:23:11,519 --> 00:23:13,920
There really is one.

270
00:23:13,920 --> 00:23:16,548
Why are you suddenly so nice to me?

271
00:23:17,719 --> 00:23:20,160
Air conditioner and chilled watermelon?

272
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:22,759
You're not just repaying me, are you?

273
00:23:22,759 --> 00:23:25,560
You're after my balance?

274
00:23:25,560 --> 00:23:29,539
- I'll take it if you don't want it.
- Don't. I'll eat it.

275
00:23:36,759 --> 00:23:39,039
It's so sweet.

276
00:23:39,039 --> 00:23:42,039
This is what summer should be like.

277
00:23:42,039 --> 00:23:43,160
To be honest,

278
00:23:43,160 --> 00:23:45,479
before coming to Zhazhating,
I really didn't know

279
00:23:45,479 --> 00:23:48,999
summer by the sea could be so hot.

280
00:23:48,999 --> 00:23:52,239
How did you spend your summers before?

281
00:23:52,239 --> 00:23:54,600
Normally.

282
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:58,360
Are you saying summer isn't normal here?

283
00:23:58,360 --> 00:24:00,279
No, that's not what I mean.

284
00:24:00,279 --> 00:24:03,239
I mean, in the past summers,
I couldn't feel the heat.

285
00:24:03,239 --> 00:24:04,800
It was cool everywhere.

286
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:06,759
Look, there was an air purifier at home.

287
00:24:06,759 --> 00:24:09,679
There was air conditioning at the malls.

288
00:24:09,679 --> 00:24:11,479
Didn't you go out?

289
00:24:11,479 --> 00:24:13,039
I had a driver.

290
00:24:13,039 --> 00:24:15,080
If it got too hot, I'd go abroad.

291
00:24:15,080 --> 00:24:17,439
I'd find a place to stay out of the heat.

292
00:24:17,439 --> 00:24:18,600
However,

293
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:20,439
most of the time,

294
00:24:20,439 --> 00:24:23,360
I'd stay at home and study with a tutor.

295
00:24:23,360 --> 00:24:26,479
Sounds like a lot of work.

296
00:24:26,479 --> 00:24:28,439
It's all right. What about you?

297
00:24:28,439 --> 00:24:30,679
Me?

298
00:24:30,679 --> 00:24:31,920
It's quite simple.

299
00:24:31,920 --> 00:24:34,039
I go back and forth between Xuan Island
and Shunyi every day.

300
00:24:34,039 --> 00:24:35,400
I do whatever I can.

301
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:36,679
If it's too hot,

302
00:24:36,679 --> 00:24:38,120
I'll take Fuzz and Hu with me.

303
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:40,708
We'll go swimming in the sea.

304
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:44,160
That's pretty wild.

305
00:24:44,160 --> 00:24:46,800
But it's quite tough.

306
00:24:49,279 --> 00:24:51,239
You went from Beijing to Zhazhating.

307
00:24:51,239 --> 00:24:53,722
It must have been tough too.

308
00:25:04,959 --> 00:25:07,120
But...

309
00:25:07,120 --> 00:25:08,719
today,

310
00:25:08,719 --> 00:25:11,840
for the first time since I got here,

311
00:25:11,840 --> 00:25:14,080
I don't feel

312
00:25:14,080 --> 00:25:16,140
it's that tough.

313
00:25:17,439 --> 00:25:19,860
Because of this used air conditioner?

314
00:25:21,239 --> 00:25:23,880
It's not just the air conditioner.

315
00:25:23,880 --> 00:25:26,199
You also changed the lock for me.

316
00:25:26,199 --> 00:25:28,439
The showerhead.

317
00:25:28,439 --> 00:25:30,039
And this chilled watermelon.

318
00:25:30,039 --> 00:25:32,942
And the laptop you fixed for me.

319
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:39,860
Also...

320
00:25:57,480 --> 00:25:59,402
I'm leaving.

321
00:26:00,120 --> 00:26:02,470
Also, thank you...

322
00:26:04,320 --> 00:26:07,635
for making this summer in Zhazhating

323
00:26:08,240 --> 00:26:10,661
less desperate.

324
00:27:12,160 --> 00:27:14,040
Who's so shameless?

325
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:16,840
Stealing clothes?

326
00:27:16,840 --> 00:27:18,519
Who's so shameless?

327
00:27:18,519 --> 00:27:21,600
Stealing a girl's clothes?

328
00:27:22,640 --> 00:27:25,310
They must be crazy poor.

329
00:27:26,880 --> 00:27:29,039
What kind of people are they?

330
00:27:29,039 --> 00:27:30,759
Tempted by a few pieces of cloth.

331
00:27:30,759 --> 00:27:32,160
Are they even human?

332
00:27:32,160 --> 00:27:35,239
What's wrong, Auntie? It's still so early.

333
00:27:35,239 --> 00:27:38,880
Your clothes... Your clothes were stolen.

334
00:27:38,880 --> 00:27:40,160
I didn't wash them.

335
00:27:40,160 --> 00:27:41,600
I did.

336
00:27:41,600 --> 00:27:44,080
Yesterday, you put your clothes there.
I just washed them.

337
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:45,880
It's all my fault. My stupid hands.

338
00:27:45,880 --> 00:27:48,959
If I hadn't washed them,
this wouldn't have happened.

339
00:27:48,959 --> 00:27:50,759
You didn't do it on purpose.

340
00:27:50,759 --> 00:27:53,519
The point is, your underwear

341
00:27:53,519 --> 00:27:55,959
is gone.

342
00:27:55,959 --> 00:27:57,160
This must be a mistake.

343
00:27:57,160 --> 00:27:59,560
Who would steal underwear?

344
00:27:59,560 --> 00:28:01,239
At Zhazhating,

345
00:28:01,239 --> 00:28:03,800
forget about underwear,

346
00:28:03,800 --> 00:28:06,480
even the copper wires on the utility poles

347
00:28:06,480 --> 00:28:08,999
might be stolen.

348
00:28:08,999 --> 00:28:11,800
Hurry up and give the clothes back!

349
00:28:11,800 --> 00:28:16,840
What are you doing?
You keep nagging all morning.

350
00:28:16,840 --> 00:28:18,640
Are you two solving a case?

351
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:20,160
Did you catch the thief?

352
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:21,360
No.

353
00:28:21,360 --> 00:28:23,439
I'm looking for them now.

354
00:28:23,439 --> 00:28:25,479
Look at this courtyard.

355
00:28:25,479 --> 00:28:27,039
It's only this big.

356
00:28:27,039 --> 00:28:29,360
There are only a few families.

357
00:28:29,360 --> 00:28:33,360
Everyone knows
who the sneaky ones are.

358
00:28:33,360 --> 00:28:35,640
I hung the laundry yesterday.

359
00:28:35,640 --> 00:28:38,167
Did you see it?

360
00:28:39,160 --> 00:28:42,479
Look, I've been crazy busy all day.

361
00:28:42,479 --> 00:28:44,920
What did you just say? You lost your laundry?

362
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:47,102
I didn't see them.

363
00:28:47,102 --> 00:28:49,880
I didn't.

364
00:28:49,880 --> 00:28:51,239
Why did you ask then?

365
00:28:51,239 --> 00:28:54,255
- Who took it? Bring it back!
- What's wrong?

366
00:28:54,255 --> 00:28:57,679
Why do people here steal everything?
Laptops and underwear.

367
00:28:57,679 --> 00:28:59,759
Don't they feel uncomfortable
wearing someone else's underwear?

368
00:28:59,759 --> 00:29:03,992
This place and I just don't get along.
This is so annoying.

369
00:29:07,120 --> 00:29:09,320
Was it hung here and stolen?

370
00:29:09,320 --> 00:29:13,322
I washed it last night and hung it here.
But it's gone today.

371
00:29:14,679 --> 00:29:17,100
So annoying.

372
00:29:43,800 --> 00:29:45,840
[Drink Together?]

373
00:30:06,320 --> 00:30:07,800
Is it good?

374
00:30:07,800 --> 00:30:09,120
It's good.

375
00:30:09,120 --> 00:30:10,719
Have some, Wu.

376
00:30:10,719 --> 00:30:12,719
Where are Qing Ye's clothes?

377
00:30:12,719 --> 00:30:14,120
I didn't steal them.

378
00:30:14,120 --> 00:30:15,439
Did I say you stole them?

379
00:30:15,439 --> 00:30:17,239
I...

380
00:30:20,560 --> 00:30:22,039
What are you doing?

381
00:30:22,039 --> 00:30:24,719
The footprints under the clothes.
What's that about?

382
00:30:24,719 --> 00:30:26,199
The footprints.

383
00:30:26,199 --> 00:30:28,279
Don't you leave footprints there
when you hang the clothes?

384
00:30:28,279 --> 00:30:30,652
What does it have to do with me?

385
00:30:32,800 --> 00:30:34,320
Xing Wu.

386
00:30:34,320 --> 00:30:36,439
Let me tell you. Don't be so shameless.

387
00:30:36,439 --> 00:30:39,039
I have a temper too. All right?

388
00:30:39,039 --> 00:30:41,080
- Wu.
- You stole the laptop too, didn't you?

389
00:30:41,080 --> 00:30:43,840
It wasn't me. It really wasn't.
I wouldn't dare.

390
00:30:43,840 --> 00:30:46,999
I only dare to steal wires.

391
00:30:46,999 --> 00:30:48,800
What are you doing?

392
00:30:48,800 --> 00:30:51,240
Wu. It's hot...

393
00:30:51,240 --> 00:30:53,360
My face... Wu!

394
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:54,600
Wu, I'm sorry.

395
00:30:54,600 --> 00:30:56,360
I'm sorry!

396
00:30:56,360 --> 00:30:57,719
Wu Lao Er.

397
00:30:57,719 --> 00:30:58,920
I'm telling you.

398
00:30:58,920 --> 00:31:00,519
Don't mess with Qing Ye.

399
00:31:00,519 --> 00:31:01,679
Or next time,

400
00:31:01,679 --> 00:31:02,999
I'll kill you.

401
00:31:02,999 --> 00:31:04,239
All right, Wu.

402
00:31:04,239 --> 00:31:07,337
I promise.

403
00:31:22,080 --> 00:31:23,679
What are you looking at?

404
00:31:23,679 --> 00:31:26,719
Never seen anyone pick up a shoe?

405
00:31:26,719 --> 00:31:30,257
Come in.

406
00:31:34,355 --> 00:31:37,880
Take your pick. Wear whatever you want.

407
00:31:37,880 --> 00:31:40,880
This is all I have.

408
00:31:40,880 --> 00:31:42,039
There's no need, Auntie.

409
00:31:42,039 --> 00:31:43,840
I just lost a piece of underwear.

410
00:31:43,840 --> 00:31:46,920
You don't have to lend me your clothes.

411
00:31:46,920 --> 00:31:50,279
You're always wearing the same few outfits.

412
00:31:50,279 --> 00:31:53,496
Did you not bring enough clothes?

413
00:31:53,496 --> 00:31:54,920
Don't worry.

414
00:31:54,920 --> 00:31:57,279
My clothes are all pretty.

415
00:31:57,279 --> 00:32:01,759
I learned my taste from your mom.

416
00:32:01,759 --> 00:32:04,679
This was the trendiest style
when I was young.

417
00:32:04,679 --> 00:32:05,959
Isn't it pretty?

418
00:32:05,959 --> 00:32:07,120
Try it on.

419
00:32:07,120 --> 00:32:09,239
- Me? No need.
- Try it on.

420
00:32:09,239 --> 00:32:11,239
- I can't.
- Try it on. It's pretty.

421
00:32:11,239 --> 00:32:12,920
Trust me.

422
00:32:12,920 --> 00:32:14,959
It looks good.

423
00:32:14,959 --> 00:32:17,880
Come out. It's fine.

424
00:32:17,880 --> 00:32:19,360
Come out.

425
00:32:19,360 --> 00:32:20,679
Wu.

426
00:32:20,679 --> 00:32:22,439
Where have you been?

427
00:32:22,439 --> 00:32:23,679
Exercising.

428
00:32:23,679 --> 00:32:24,800
You're back just in time.

429
00:32:24,800 --> 00:32:25,920
Well...

430
00:32:25,920 --> 00:32:29,640
Ye's a bit unsure. You can help her decide.

431
00:32:29,640 --> 00:32:31,570
What do you mean?

432
00:32:32,199 --> 00:32:34,233
Just come out. Come out.

433
00:32:34,233 --> 00:32:35,800
My clothes look nice.

434
00:32:35,800 --> 00:32:38,595
What do you think? Does she look nice?

435
00:32:39,279 --> 00:32:42,600
- Why are you laughing?
- You can choose not to say anything.

436
00:32:42,600 --> 00:32:44,962
I'll keep quiet.

437
00:32:46,279 --> 00:32:48,320
Change. Let's change.

438
00:32:48,320 --> 00:32:50,039
We'll keep going until you're happy.

439
00:32:50,039 --> 00:32:54,840
Let's go. I've been saving these clothes.

440
00:32:54,840 --> 00:32:57,005
Xing Wu.

441
00:32:57,719 --> 00:33:00,503
Take a look. What do you think?

442
00:33:07,439 --> 00:33:09,239
Got it. Change again.

443
00:33:09,239 --> 00:33:11,158
Let's go.

444
00:33:31,719 --> 00:33:32,759
How about

445
00:33:32,759 --> 00:33:35,120
I do it myself.

446
00:33:35,120 --> 00:33:39,739
Okay. Pick what you like.
Wear whatever you want.

447
00:33:45,320 --> 00:33:47,625
Doesn't it look good?

448
00:34:18,560 --> 00:34:21,439
What do you think, Auntie?

449
00:34:21,439 --> 00:34:25,260
You look like my sister back then.

450
00:34:27,280 --> 00:34:29,599
Your legs are so long.

451
00:34:29,599 --> 00:34:32,272
It's beautiful.

452
00:34:37,760 --> 00:34:40,652
Mom. Come out for a second.

453
00:34:43,519 --> 00:34:44,920
What is it?

454
00:34:44,920 --> 00:34:48,479
Later, go and buy some clothes for Qing Ye.

455
00:34:48,479 --> 00:34:50,557
- I'm busy.
- Play less mahjong.

456
00:34:50,557 --> 00:34:54,200
- Then you'll be free.
- Pocky's son is getting married tomorrow.

457
00:34:54,200 --> 00:34:55,959
So tonight, they're having
the Pre-Wedding Banquet.

458
00:34:55,959 --> 00:34:58,640
I promised Hu's mom and Fuzz's mom
I'd go over to help.

459
00:34:58,640 --> 00:35:01,418
I have to go soon.

460
00:35:01,418 --> 00:35:03,039
Are you in a hurry?

461
00:35:03,039 --> 00:35:06,953
I am. Look. She's rushing me.

462
00:35:08,599 --> 00:35:09,840
Just let her wear mine.

463
00:35:09,840 --> 00:35:11,200
Who's going to buy it for her?

464
00:35:11,200 --> 00:35:13,599
Figure it out yourself.

465
00:35:13,599 --> 00:35:15,639
I'll take Grandma there first.

466
00:35:15,639 --> 00:35:17,680
You take Ye there later.

467
00:35:17,680 --> 00:35:19,680
We gave a wedding gift.

468
00:35:19,680 --> 00:35:23,730
- We're going to eat our money's worth.
- Again?

469
00:35:25,119 --> 00:35:28,159
<i>Two hands in the sky.</i>

470
00:35:29,159 --> 00:35:31,660
<i>Up.</i>

471
00:35:36,920 --> 00:35:38,780
<i>Down.</i>

472
00:35:39,720 --> 00:35:42,200
You know Baduanjin?

473
00:35:42,200 --> 00:35:45,463
I just started learning it three minutes ago.

474
00:35:47,920 --> 00:35:49,680
I'm going to the county to buy something.

475
00:35:49,680 --> 00:35:51,439
Do you want to join me?

476
00:35:51,439 --> 00:35:53,200
It's okay.

477
00:35:53,200 --> 00:35:55,639
I lost my laptop and clothes
as soon as I got here.

478
00:35:55,639 --> 00:35:57,920
I think before I leave,

479
00:35:57,920 --> 00:36:00,720
I'll practice the Turtle Breathing Technique

480
00:36:00,720 --> 00:36:03,089
to calm down and recharge.

481
00:36:04,240 --> 00:36:06,200
Okay. I'll get going then.

482
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:08,167
Wait.

483
00:36:09,360 --> 00:36:10,760
You...

484
00:36:10,760 --> 00:36:12,559
Well...

485
00:36:12,559 --> 00:36:15,500
Can you bring me...

486
00:36:19,599 --> 00:36:21,360
the clothes underneath?

487
00:36:21,360 --> 00:36:23,401
Do you understand?

488
00:36:24,200 --> 00:36:26,639
The ones that come in no size.

489
00:36:26,639 --> 00:36:28,775
Okay.

490
00:37:00,920 --> 00:37:03,200
- Hey.
<i>- Wu, I have a job for you.</i>

491
00:37:03,200 --> 00:37:04,200
<i>See you at Shunyi.</i>

492
00:37:04,200 --> 00:37:06,599
Did you put a camera on me?

493
00:37:06,599 --> 00:37:07,599
<i>What do you mean?</i>

494
00:37:07,599 --> 00:37:08,840
Nothing.

495
00:37:08,840 --> 00:37:10,694
I'll be right there.

496
00:37:11,280 --> 00:37:13,400
My sister got you this job.

497
00:37:14,320 --> 00:37:16,559
Isn't your sister
on a business trip in Hainan?

498
00:37:16,559 --> 00:37:17,840
She knows you need money.

499
00:37:17,840 --> 00:37:19,360
She's been keeping an eye out for you.

500
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:20,599
My sister treats you

501
00:37:20,599 --> 00:37:22,800
better than me, her own brother.

502
00:37:22,800 --> 00:37:25,039
Don't sugarcoat it. Get to the point.

503
00:37:25,039 --> 00:37:26,439
What's going on with this job?

504
00:37:26,439 --> 00:37:28,320
Mr. Ye is my sister's boss.

505
00:37:28,320 --> 00:37:31,800
His son wants someone to build him
a model aircraft for a competition.

506
00:37:31,800 --> 00:37:33,600
My sister recommended you.

507
00:37:33,600 --> 00:37:36,152
An oil-powered model aircraft?

508
00:37:40,320 --> 00:37:42,880
But I don't know much about it.

509
00:37:42,880 --> 00:37:45,240
What model aircraft can't you build?

510
00:37:45,240 --> 00:37:46,800
Master one, master all.

511
00:37:46,800 --> 00:37:49,639
It can't be that hard.

512
00:37:49,639 --> 00:37:51,200
I don't have much theoretical knowledge.

513
00:37:51,200 --> 00:37:54,119
Maintaining the aircraft's flexibility
and maneuverability

514
00:37:54,119 --> 00:37:55,880
is not easy.

515
00:37:55,880 --> 00:37:57,639
With your sister's resources and connections,

516
00:37:57,639 --> 00:38:00,200
it shouldn't be hard
to find an expert in this field.

517
00:38:00,200 --> 00:38:03,840
They're nothing compared to you.

518
00:38:03,840 --> 00:38:06,794
What do you think, Wu?
Do you want to do it?

519
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:13,240
It's not cheap to make this kind of model.

520
00:38:13,240 --> 00:38:14,240
My sister said,

521
00:38:14,240 --> 00:38:15,320
as long as you do a good job,

522
00:38:15,320 --> 00:38:17,500
the price is not a problem.

523
00:38:20,479 --> 00:38:22,240
It's 8,000 yuan.

524
00:38:22,240 --> 00:38:24,680
I'll talk to my sister.

525
00:38:32,753 --> 00:38:35,599
She said it's a deal.

526
00:38:35,599 --> 00:38:38,119
Okay. Thank your sister for me.

527
00:38:38,119 --> 00:38:39,479
Thank her in person.

528
00:38:39,479 --> 00:38:41,980
She might be happier.

529
00:39:01,967 --> 00:39:04,848
Are you really giving up?

530
00:39:05,559 --> 00:39:07,479
I'll stay motionless until provoked.

531
00:39:07,479 --> 00:39:09,815
Then I won't be defeated.

532
00:39:10,400 --> 00:39:11,880
When you fought with me before,

533
00:39:11,880 --> 00:39:14,639
I thought you were full of rebelliousness.

534
00:39:14,639 --> 00:39:15,999
Full of rebelliousness?

535
00:39:15,999 --> 00:39:18,079
I don't even have clothes to wear.

536
00:39:18,079 --> 00:39:21,192
My online order won't be here for a few days.

537
00:39:22,240 --> 00:39:23,760
This is...

538
00:39:23,760 --> 00:39:26,612
This should be what you want.

539
00:39:28,720 --> 00:39:30,240
Try it on later and see if it fits.

540
00:39:30,240 --> 00:39:32,395
If it doesn't, I'll go change it.

541
00:39:33,119 --> 00:39:35,066
All right.

542
00:39:37,079 --> 00:39:39,720
Can you get up and move now?

543
00:39:39,720 --> 00:39:42,079
- Why?
- Pocky's son is getting married.

544
00:39:42,079 --> 00:39:44,439
I'm taking you to get some good luck
and get rid of the bad luck.

545
00:39:44,439 --> 00:39:46,080
You get married at night here?

546
00:39:46,080 --> 00:39:47,720
It's not a formal wedding.

547
00:39:47,720 --> 00:39:48,999
The night before the wedding,

548
00:39:48,999 --> 00:39:51,845
we treat the neighbors to drinks.

549
00:39:52,599 --> 00:39:55,959
- Wu!
- Qing Ye!

550
00:39:55,959 --> 00:39:58,079
Qing Ye! Wu!

551
00:39:58,079 --> 00:39:59,080
Qing Ye!

552
00:39:59,080 --> 00:40:01,926
Let's go to the feast!

553
00:40:03,280 --> 00:40:04,439
Go, go, go!

554
00:40:04,439 --> 00:40:07,240
Let's go!

555
00:40:07,240 --> 00:40:09,840
Are you coming?

556
00:40:12,559 --> 00:40:14,320
They're here.

557
00:40:14,320 --> 00:40:17,039
- Congratulations.
- Good.

558
00:40:17,039 --> 00:40:19,240
Get ready.

559
00:40:19,240 --> 00:40:20,800
You're here.

560
00:40:20,800 --> 00:40:23,305
Thank you.

561
00:40:24,959 --> 00:40:27,240
Fen'er, tell them to serve
the cold dishes first.

562
00:40:27,240 --> 00:40:29,680
- All right.
- Hu's mom.

563
00:40:29,680 --> 00:40:32,360
Honey, serve the cold dishes first.

564
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:33,800
Come on.

565
00:40:33,800 --> 00:40:35,559
Yu, is the water boiling?

566
00:40:35,559 --> 00:40:37,519
Yeah, it's boiling soon.

567
00:40:37,519 --> 00:40:39,320
Lower the heat.

568
00:40:39,320 --> 00:40:41,939
The dishes are coming.

569
00:40:43,280 --> 00:40:45,360
You can have some candies.

570
00:40:45,360 --> 00:40:47,760
Here. Okay, come on.

571
00:40:47,760 --> 00:40:50,720
Thank you, everyone. Thank you.

572
00:40:50,720 --> 00:40:53,639
- The food is here.
- Ribs.

573
00:40:53,639 --> 00:40:54,720
Have a seat.

574
00:40:54,720 --> 00:40:56,439
Come on. Have a seat.

575
00:40:56,439 --> 00:40:57,999
Have some peanuts and melon seeds.

576
00:40:57,999 --> 00:40:59,639
Have a seat and have some food.

577
00:40:59,639 --> 00:41:01,079
Have a seat.

578
00:41:01,079 --> 00:41:03,000
Have a seat, everyone. Thank you.

579
00:41:03,000 --> 00:41:05,710
Thank you.

580
00:41:15,953 --> 00:41:18,639
That's a lot of work.

581
00:41:18,639 --> 00:41:19,999
Are you impressed?

582
00:41:19,999 --> 00:41:22,999
This is the scale of a banquet in Zhazhating.

583
00:41:22,999 --> 00:41:25,479
It's an eye-opener.

584
00:41:25,479 --> 00:41:27,559
Wu, Qing Ye.

585
00:41:27,559 --> 00:41:28,999
- This way.
- Where?

586
00:41:28,999 --> 00:41:30,639
Over there. This way.

587
00:41:30,639 --> 00:41:32,240
Let's go.

588
00:41:32,240 --> 00:41:33,959
Wu, Qing Ye, you're here. Have a seat.

589
00:41:33,959 --> 00:41:35,200
The banquet is about to start.

590
00:41:35,200 --> 00:41:37,959
Take good care of them.

591
00:41:37,959 --> 00:41:40,213
Have a seat. I'll drink with you today.

592
00:41:40,213 --> 00:41:41,559
Let's have a drink.

593
00:41:41,559 --> 00:41:43,079
- Let's eat.
- I'll be right back.

594
00:41:43,079 --> 00:41:44,119
Qing Ye, what would you like to drink?

595
00:41:44,119 --> 00:41:45,439
Beer.

596
00:41:45,439 --> 00:41:47,720
Can you drink?
Why don't you have a soft drink?

597
00:41:47,720 --> 00:41:51,039
- I'm an adult.
- We all are. I have a driver's license.

598
00:41:51,039 --> 00:41:54,065
Have a seat.

599
00:42:01,119 --> 00:42:03,119
What are you looking at?

600
00:42:03,119 --> 00:42:05,079
Gang. Here.

601
00:42:05,079 --> 00:42:06,720
Take it back.

602
00:42:06,720 --> 00:42:08,159
The laptop you sold me...

603
00:42:08,159 --> 00:42:09,360
Where did you steal it from?

604
00:42:09,360 --> 00:42:11,439
From the woman next to Xing Wu?

605
00:42:11,439 --> 00:42:14,400
No, Gang. I... I didn't steal it.

606
00:42:14,400 --> 00:42:15,920
How can you say that?

607
00:42:15,920 --> 00:42:17,639
Right. You didn't steal it.

608
00:42:17,639 --> 00:42:20,159
She gave it to you.

609
00:42:20,159 --> 00:42:22,494
Wait, Gang.

610
00:42:26,439 --> 00:42:28,519
Friends and family.

611
00:42:28,519 --> 00:42:30,039
Folks and neighbors.

612
00:42:30,039 --> 00:42:35,519
I'd like to thank everyone
for coming despite your busy schedules.

613
00:42:35,519 --> 00:42:38,439
My wife and I thank you all.
Thank you, everyone.

614
00:42:38,439 --> 00:42:41,439
Great!

615
00:42:41,439 --> 00:42:44,559
So let me just say this:

616
00:42:44,559 --> 00:42:45,559
Eat well.

617
00:42:45,559 --> 00:42:46,880
Drink well.

618
00:42:46,880 --> 00:42:48,119
Let the banquet begin.

619
00:42:48,119 --> 00:42:50,079
- Yeah!
- All right.

620
00:42:50,079 --> 00:42:51,760
- Let's eat.
- Let's go.

621
00:42:51,760 --> 00:42:53,599
Come on. The feast is here.

622
00:42:53,599 --> 00:42:55,159
Here.

623
00:42:55,159 --> 00:42:57,739
Have a drink.

624
00:42:59,039 --> 00:43:00,280
Is wedding food

625
00:43:00,280 --> 00:43:02,439
always this hearty here?

626
00:43:02,439 --> 00:43:03,519
Of course.

627
00:43:03,519 --> 00:43:05,079
Marriage is a big deal in life.

628
00:43:05,079 --> 00:43:06,119
The spread has to be top-notch.

629
00:43:06,119 --> 00:43:08,079
This dish is what we save

630
00:43:08,079 --> 00:43:09,680
for festivals in Zhazhating.

631
00:43:09,680 --> 00:43:11,039
Called 'Destined Love'.

632
00:43:11,039 --> 00:43:12,639
Braised sea cucumber with pork tendon.

633
00:43:12,639 --> 00:43:14,599
What about that one?

634
00:43:14,599 --> 00:43:18,360
'Match Made in Heaven'.

635
00:43:18,360 --> 00:43:21,439
They all have auspicious names.

636
00:43:21,439 --> 00:43:24,231
It looks delicious.

637
00:43:26,672 --> 00:43:28,479
Qing Ye, this is

638
00:43:28,479 --> 00:43:30,439
how we do it here.

639
00:43:30,439 --> 00:43:32,439
Quick hands get the food.
Slow hands get none.

640
00:43:32,439 --> 00:43:34,360
A new dish is here.

641
00:43:34,360 --> 00:43:36,360
Come on.

642
00:43:36,360 --> 00:43:38,780
I'll get right to it then.

643
00:43:41,200 --> 00:43:43,523
You're so happy.

